Brell Serilis Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukulanaesoulsease.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kulanae Soulsease</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/27/01 11:18:26 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.wwa.com/~danas/Kulanae4.jpg width=119 height=158></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bards on crowd control</span><hr size=1> Let's face facts here.  At most a skilled Bard can &quot;reliably&quot; mez 3 MOBs.  You can try four but if you get one resist you get a cascade of mez breaks which can mean an early grave.  There is NO WAY I will EVER be as good at mezing as a Chanter.  Pure and simple.  To say otherwise is to give people a really false impression of what a Bard can truely do and serve to fan the &quot;nerf the uber-Bards&quot; mentality.<br>
