<br>
<i>Joy is in the ears that hear!</i>
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uazzimezzcaline.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azzi Mezzcaline</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/28/01 3:27:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bards on crowd control</span><hr size=1> One of the coolest things I've seen EVER!! I'm a chanter played a shaman to 42 and a few other characters to just over 20.. Fell in love with the chanter class!! Anyways, a bard doing CC when the chanter is busy doing some CC a little away for the group or the chanter IS oom.. Yes before C2 and theft of thought a chanter can run out of mana!!! I was very impressed with a bard cannot remember her name but I let her know how awesome it was for me to be oom and have someone cover the 3 mobs we had on us in karnor's!! I won't go back to karnor's until post 50 because I don't have the mana pool to hold a room and cover the trains that pass us. But YES as long as I'm working with the bard (chatting letting each other know what's going on) the group is better off!! Aside from that I've seen a bard camp choon and froon in WK .. I tried it once .. heheh failed miserably! the second time I tried I was too high to appreciate the exp on it! .. Bards have multiple roles they can fill and are always welcome to any team I'm in!!  <p><img src=http://www.geocities.com/etherealknighthood/signat.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquemnwyndrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quemn Wyndrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/28/01 10:15:40 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/M75130?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=80&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bards on crowd control</span><hr size=1> in most situations, in sebilis, karnor, charasis, chardok, you dont have more than 4 total mobs at 1 time. ive done crowd control for all of these places, an enchanter without something to teft of thought off of cannot hold more than 3 mezed for very long either, and they die a lot faster. <p><center><b>Quemn Wyndrunner</b></center>
