I have had experiences with bards on a few Kael raids helping with charm, that was very helpful. I can't say I have really had the pleasure of a bard helping with mez though.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquemnwyndrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quemn Wyndrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Assist Dammit!</span><br>  Posts: 279<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/30/01 3:26:49 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/M75130?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=80&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bards on crowd control</span><hr size=1> mebbe ive just seen too many bad enchanters in karnor :laugh <p><center><b>Quemn Wyndrunner</b></center>
