<center><a href=mailto:starpunk111@hotmail.com>Email Me</a></center>



</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchants.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chants</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lord Chancellor of Brell</span><br>  Posts: 467<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/31/01 8:57:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bards on crowd control</span><hr size=1> There is absolutely no question that a bard is very good at crowd control at level 53+.<br>
<br>
I soloed the zone into Howling stones for an hour a few days ago.  Masterrloo and I were going to do the zone in alone, but he died, and I was down to less than a bub of hits with two sepulcher skeletons on me.  When Sadara got there an hour later, I had managed to kill these two of the skeletons, and had two mezzed which had spawned later.  I was also at full hits.<br>
<br>
I have mezzed stuff on PoG, rock golems in Hole, and been a replacement enchanter for sebilis a few times.<br>
<br>
There is no question that people don't really understand how strong bard mez is.  I have had clerics and shamans in the group do root park on mobs when it has been completely unecessary -- and this was after I had said many times that I could mez.  They don't care.  They are used to doing things thier way.  They just want bards to play mana song.<br>
<br>
It is possible for a bard to keep two mobs mezzed, to keep mana song up, and to keep the tanks hasted.  It is possible to keep three mobs mezzed and maybe weave in an occasional mana song or haste, and it's not that tricky.  Four mobs will take all of my concentration, but it can be done.<br>
<br>
Bard mez is mana free.  It takes 3 seconds to cast, which means you need to wait 9 seconds minimum to have three mobs mezzed.  You need to target each mob, so separating the /assist mob from the others is important.  If you are grouped with a bard doing crowd control, DO NOT RUN AROUND if a mob breaks mez and is on you.  He will be mezzed in about 1-4 seconds later, depending on where he is on the bard's mez cycle.  Running around makes it VERY hard to target.  Any unecessary delay in targeting disrupts the bards mez cycle and the other mobs break free.<br>
<br>
