<br>
A bard mez cycle is the sequence of mobs that a bard is mezzing.  Here is how it works.  Let's say four mobs are pulled.  A bard will proabably run kinda close the the puller target and mez one.  One down.  By that time, the other three are in the camp.  The bard will then target and mez a second one.  Two down, but the first one will have mezz wear off soon.  Target the third, and mez.  Even while the bard waits for the third one to be mezzed, he or she will generally target the first mob, wait for mez to take effect on the third one, then mez the first one.  He will then repeat the cycle again.  That is the bard mez cycle.<br>
<br>
Speed in targeting is very imprtant, because while the song is powerful, it lasts for about 9 seconds.  If a bard has to waste time targeting a mob, then his or her cycle is disrupted.<br>
<br>
